The paper deals with graph algorithms and enumeration, which are common topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and data structures (cs.DS). The algorithm presented in the paper involves triangulations of graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also mentions tree decompositions, which are relevant to both theoretical computer science (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as they are used in various applications such as planning and optimization.
